Females Weights

Frederico Kiffer, PhD

Import Libraries

library(tidyverse)
library(colorspace)
library(ggpubr)
library(rstatix)

Load CSV Data

AllFemalesWeights <- read_csv("AllFemalesWeights.csv")

Dataframe Preview

head(AllFemalesWeights, 10)

Defining Factor Variables

AllFemalesWeights <- AllFemalesWeights %>%
  convert_as_factor(Radiation, Mouse)

Calculate Mean and SEM by Day

AllFemalesWeights %>%
  group_by(Radiation, Weeks) %>%
  get_summary_stats(Weight, type = "mean_se")

BoxPlot

ActiveBox <- ggboxplot(
  AllFemalesWeights, x = "Weeks", y = "Weight",
  color = "Radiation", palette = c("#ef5e4f", "#50caee")) +
  ggtitle("Male Weigths Box Plots") +
  xlab("Date")
  ylab("Weight (g)")
## $y
## [1] "Weight (g)"
## 
## attr(,"class")
## [1] "labels"
ActiveBox

Identify Outliers

AllFemalesWeightsOutliers <- AllFemalesWeights %>%
  group_by(Radiation, Weeks) %>%
  identify_outliers(Weight)
AllFemalesWeightsOutliers

Drop Samples with Less than 3 Measurements

AllFemalesWeightsClean <- AllFemalesWeights
AllFemalesWeightsClean %>%
  group_by(Mouse) %>%
  filter(n() >=3)

Test for Normality of Distribution

AllFemalesWeightsClean %>%
  group_by(Radiation, Weeks) %>%
  shapiro_test(Weight)

Visualize Distribution by QQPlots

ggqqplot(AllFemalesWeights, "Weight", ggtheme = theme_bw()) +
  facet_grid(Radiation ~ Weeks, labeller = "label_both")

Test for Homogeneity of Variance

AllFemalesWeights %>%
  group_by(Weeks) %>%
  levene_test(Weight ~ Radiation)

Repeated Measures ANOVA with Greenhouse-Geisser Corrections

AllFemalesANOVA <- anova_test(
  data = AllFemalesWeights, 
  Weight ~ Radiation * Weeks, 
  wid = Mouse
)
get_anova_table(AllFemalesANOVA)

Multiple Comparisons with Bonferroni Corrections

AllFemalesPairwise <- AllFemalesWeights %>%
  group_by(Weeks) %>%
  pairwise_t_test(
    Weight ~ Radiation, paired = FALSE,
    p.adjust.method = "bonferroni"
  )
AllFemalesPairwise

Main Effect Size

FemaleWeightsES <- AllFemalesWeights %>%
  group_by(Weeks) %>%
  convert_as_factor(Weeks)
eta_squared(aov(Weight ~ Radiation, data = FemaleWeightsES))
##    Radiation 
## 6.627854e-05

Multiple Comparisons Effect Sizes

cohens_d(Weight ~ Radiation, data = FemaleWeightsES)

Line Graph

AllFemalesGraph <- ggplot(AllFemalesWeights, aes(x=Weeks, 
    y=Weight, group=Radiation, 
    fill=Radiation, color=Radiation)) +
    geom_point(size = 1, alpha = 0) +
    geom_smooth(span = .4, aes(color=Radiation, fill=Radiation)) +
   scale_fill_manual(values = c( "#ef5e4f", "#50caee"))+
    scale_color_manual(values = c("#ef5e4f", "#50caee"))+
  ggtitle("Female Weights") + 
  ylab("Weight (g)") + 
  xlab("Date (from 2019)") +
  scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0,0)) +
  #scale_x_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0,0))) +#makes x axis start at 1
  coord_cartesian(expand = FALSE, ylim = c(0,50)) + #does not remove points outside of y-limit, merges y-axis with line graph
  scale_x_date(date_labels = "%b %d", date_breaks = "2 month") + #scales x axis by date, evert 2 months
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
      plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face="bold", size = 18), 
      panel.background = element_blank(), 
      axis.line = element_line(colour = "black", size = 1), 
      axis.text=element_text(colour = "black", family="Arial", size=12,
                             face="bold"), 
      axis.title.x=element_text(face = "bold", size=14),
      axis.title.y=element_text(face = "bold", size=14),
      legend.title=element_text(face="bold"),
      legend.text=element_text(face="bold")) 
print(AllFemalesGraph)
